<p>So it's all about your own audience and scenario, right.</p>
<h2>Main issues these days:</h2>

<h3>Essentials</h3>
<p>These things I consider fairly essential to support if you're planning on catering to legacy browser users. Usage of flexbox, box-sizing and rem units could really impact the usability of a site if fallbacks are not provided.</p>
<p>I use quite a lot of SVGs in my projects as it's fairly well supported and just looks so nice on high resolution displays! However it could affect the accessibility of a site if no fallback images are provided.</p>

