{{#content "post-tldr"}}
<p>I've fully dropped support for IE8 and below due to having a negligible number of visitors using these browsers in the last year.</p>
<p>Due to this, I've been able to use relative units for font and layout sizing, use SVGs for images and background textures, and upgrade to jQuery 2.0 - which has dropped support for legacy browsers also.</p>
<p>The above shows my reasons for the browser compatibility decisions I made and documents how I <em>learned to stop worrying and dropped legacy browser support</em>.</p>
<p>I urge you to rigorously assess your own situation and learn to stop worrying too!</p>

